{
  "texts": [
    "NSGA-II's ability to find a set of optimal solutions, each balancing the objectives differently, provides an overview of the solution space, ensuring no potential optimal configuration is overlooked.• Elitism and Diversity Preservation: One of NSGA-II's main features is its elitism mechanism, which ensures that the best solutions are always carried forward to the next generation without being lost due to selection pressure.",
    "This aspect is crucial for our study, where preserving high-quality solutions across generations can accelerate convergence towards optimal configurations.",
    "Additionally, NSGA-II incorporates a diversity-preserving operator known as crowding distance.",
    "This operator ensures a diverse population by maintaining individuals that are spread out across the entire Pareto front, thus preventing premature convergence to sub-optimal regions of the solution space.• Scalability and Computational Efficiency: NSGA-II demonstrates scalability and computational efficiency compared to its predecessors and many contemporary algorithms.",
    "Its fast non-dominated sorting approach, coupled with a simple yet effective crowding distance calculation, allows NSGA-II to handle large populations and high-dimensional spaces efficiently."
  ]
}